Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Men's Health Recommendations: Monitor and visit your doctor if you experience any urinary symptoms.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Employee: Robert Leon
Report Date: 2020-11-03
Doctor: Christie Pilossof
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new worrying or persistent urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.

Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
Comment Key: WomensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Cholesterol levels: continue taking simvastatin and try to manage with lifestyle factors. Increase exercise again once able to, watch the carbs and sugar in your diet, manage stress levels and take omega 3 supplements 2g daily. Repeat blood after 3 months.
